#: ../../preinstall.rst:205
# dbdf069cf38c48d0bf5056473952ecdc
msgid "Obtaining PC-BSD®"
msgstr ""

#: ../../preinstall.rst:207
# d7348ee5a70646a89c80c450960c465d
msgid "PC-BSD® version numbers are similar to those used by FreeBSD. In addition, PC-BSD® provides two branches. The branch that you choose to install or upgrade to determines when you will receive updates as new features and drivers are added to the operating system. Downloadable image names include the version number, where |version| is the most recent version, and either the word :file:`RELEASE` or :file:`STABLE`, where:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../preinstall.rst:211
# 232ae74ec07146928e405cffa4049e3e
msgid "**RELEASE:** indicates that new drivers and features will not be added to the operating system until the next RELEASE version becomes available and the user upgrades to that new version. If reliability is more important to you than new features or drivers, use the RELEASE version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../preinstall.rst:214
# 498e29da97244dd098ae8682a65764cc
msgid "**STABLE:** around the 1st of each month, :ref:`Update Manager` will provide a patch which will update the operating system to include all of the new features and drivers. If you wish to have or test the latest features and drivers as they become available and can tolerate possible breakage caused by new features being available before the next RELEASE, use the STABLE version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../preinstall.rst:218
# bae0b366101649119d03c1cb3763f4df
msgid "The image files for the current RELEASE can be downloaded from the `PC-BSD® website <http://www.pcbsd.org/en/download.html>`_. Previous RELEASE versions and STABLE versions can be downloaded from the `PC-BSD® CDN <http://iso.cdn.pcbsd.org/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../preinstall.rst:221
# a246f094363f4571865e5c2bb9a2b5ad
msgid "Several types of files are available for download. Before downloading a file, review the following descriptions to see which one best suits your needs:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../preinstall.rst:223
# 51e18b12cd9545dcba219a61d131dca5
msgid "Files beginning with :file:`PCBSD` and ending in :file:`DVD-USB.iso` contain all of the information needed to install a graphical desktop or command-line server as well as several applications during installation. This type of file can either be burned to a DVD media or a USB thumb drive. There will also be associated files with the same name but ending in a :file:`.md5` or :file:`.sha256` extension. Depending upon your current operating system and its tools, you can use the value in either one of those files to determine the integrity of the download, as described in :ref:`Data Integrity Check`. If a torrent is available, there will also be a file with the same name and a :file:`.torrent` extension."
msgstr ""

#: ../../preinstall.rst:229
# 913f18d9be174cb3bf732870c6ee8d83
msgid "Files beginning with :file:`TrueOS` contain a command-line installer and are used to install a command-line version of a server. This type of file can either be burned to a CD media or a USB thumb drive. There will also be associated files with the same name but ending in a :file:`.md5` or :file:`.sha256` extension. Depending upon your current operating system and its tools, you can use the value in either one of those files to determine the integrity of the download, as described in :ref:`Data Integrity Check`. If a torrent is available, there will also be a file with the same name and a :file:`.torrent` extension."
msgstr ""

#: ../../preinstall.rst:235
# 892ef246f4b247dcad2ad760b8adbaa6
msgid "Files containing :file:`netinstall` in their name are used to perform a network install. These files can be burned to a CD, so are a smaller initial download size. However, they require an Internet connection during installation as the files needed by the installer will be downloaded from the Internet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../preinstall.rst:238
# 388a714fb5d24d0fb4e262886c2348c2
msgid "If you plan to install a graphical desktop, download the file with :file:`PCBSD` in its name and either burn it to a DVD media or write it to a removable USB device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../preinstall.rst:241
# 06c31d6eca4c459b90c3e46d5d4804b2
msgid "If you prefer to install a command-line only server, you can either download the same ISO or download the ISO with :file:`TRUEOS` in the name. The :file:`TRUEOS` download is smaller and can be burned to a CD or written to a removable USB device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../preinstall.rst:244
